1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
I have the pleasure to present to you,

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:05,120
Dr. Martin Luther King, dear.

3
00:00:05,120 --> 00:00:13,120
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

4
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:23,240
I am happy to join with you today in what will go down in history

5
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:28,720
as the greatest demonstration for freedom in the history of our nation.

6
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:37,680
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

7
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:49,560
Five score years ago, a great American in whose symbolic shadow we stand today,

8
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:55,480
signed the Emancipation Proclamation.

9
00:00:55,480 --> 00:01:05,120
This momentous decree came as a great beacon light of hope to millions of Negro slaves

10
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:11,480
who had been seared in the flames of withering injustice.

11
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:21,960
It came as a joyous daybreak to end the long night of their captivity.

12
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:32,800
But one hundred years later, the Negro steel is not free.

13
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:40,080
One hundred years later, the life of the Negro steel satly crippled

14
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:47,080
by the manacles of segregation and the chains of discrimination,

15
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:55,200
one hundred years later, the Negro lives on a lonely island of poverty

16
00:01:55,200 --> 00:02:00,200
in the midst of a vast ocean of material prosperity.

